PN,31813
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1774947927
OL,3,CWhy the US could be setting its sights
OL,4,Con Kharg Island
OL,6,FThe near closure of the Strait of
OL,7,FHormuz has seen oil prices surge to
OL,8,Fmore than $100 a barrel continuously
OL,9,Fsince the war began, with the world's
OL,10,Femergency oil system releasing a
OL,11,Frecord 400 million barrels to combat
OL,12,Fthe spike.
OL,14,FWhat has the White House said?
OL,16,FTrump said the US was weighing up an
OL,17,Finvasion of Kharg Island in an
OL,18,Finterview published by the Financial
OL,19,FTimes on Monday, telling reporters:
OL,20,F"My favourite thing is to take the oil
OL,21,Fin Iran".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31814
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1774947927
OL,3,CWhy the US could be setting its sights
OL,4,Con Kharg Island
OL,6,F"Maybe we take Kharg Island, maybe we
OL,7,Fdon't. We have a lot of options. It
OL,8,Fwould also mean we had to be there for
OL,9,Fa while," Trump said.
OL,11,FThe president also said he thought
OL,12,FKharg did not have "any defence",
OL,13,Fclaiming the US could take it "very
OL,14,Feasily".
OL,16,FThe US has sent thousands of troops to
OL,17,Fthe region over the past week, despite
OL,18,FTrump stating continuously that
OL,19,Fnegotiations with Iran had begun and
OL,20,Fwere going "very well".
